-- Generated by db/gen_populate2.py from resources/{caterers,sessions,students}.xlsx
-- plus the data baked in to that script from caterer-contacts.pdf, caterer-menus.pdf,
-- exclusions.pdf and absences.pdf. Do not edit by hand — re-run the generator.
-- Assumes a clean DB (run db/reset.sql then db/schema.sql first).

-- Caterers → IDs 1..4

-- Pricing structures (1:1 with caterers)

-- Menu items per caterer. H added to every dish whose name does not contain
-- 'pork' or 'bacon' (assume non-pork = halal). A source VO (vegetarian option)
-- dish is split into two orderable items: the default version (no V tag) and a
-- '... (vegetarian)' version that carries the V tag, since VO means the caterer
-- can prepare it vegetarian on request rather than it being vegetarian by default.

-- Schools. caterer_id assigned per sessions.xlsx (each school currently uses one caterer).

-- Programs (weekly recurring slots). Derived from sessions.xlsx by grouping rows
-- on (school, day-of-week). Each program inherits manager/time/year-levels from
-- one of its rows (they're consistent within a (school, day) group in the source).

-- Sessions: one row per dated session from sessions.xlsx. sub_manager_* populated
-- only when the session's manager differs from the program's regular manager.
-- Whole-session exclusions (per exclusions.pdf) are skipped here.

-- Students. Deduplicated across all sheets in students.xlsx by student_email.

-- Enrolments: student → program. A student appearing in multiple sheets is
-- enrolled in multiple programs (e.g. attends Mon and Tue).

-- Manager-submitted feedback per caterer. Dish names match the menu so an LLM
-- can derive per-dish quality signals.

-- Dish ratings: per-student 1-10 scores collected by tutors during each past
-- session. One dietary-appropriate dish rated per student per delivery night.

-- Absences: explicit absences from absences.pdf plus year-level exclusions
-- (exclusions.pdf) expanded into individual absent students.

-- Student pre-ordered meals: a locked-in dish for an upcoming session, for a
-- subset of eligible students; the rest are auto-assigned from the dish ranking.
